00:00:55.720 --> 00:00:58.439
and you can read and study and see all that God does,

00:00:59.180 --> 00:01:00.900
revival, and so on and so forth,

00:01:00.900 --> 00:01:04.540
and we find that as we come to the book of Nehemiah,

00:01:04.540 --> 00:01:06.139
that it's in that same time frame,

00:01:06.139 --> 00:01:09.180
obviously several years after Ezra and that group,

00:01:09.180 --> 00:01:11.860
that original group had returned to Jerusalem,

00:01:11.860 --> 00:01:14.220
and many years later, we find that Nehemiah

00:01:14.220 --> 00:01:17.260
in chapter number one is found in Shushan,

00:01:17.260 --> 00:01:20.779
and he's serving the king Artaxerxes,

00:01:20.779 --> 00:01:22.500
and we find that he's in that place,

00:01:22.500 --> 00:01:24.699
and he's the cupbearer for Artaxerxes,

00:01:24.699 --> 00:01:26.819
and chapter number one tells us

00:01:26.839 --> 00:01:30.000
that he has some correspondence with Hanani,

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:32.839
and the specifics of that correspondence

00:01:32.839 --> 00:01:36.519
dealt with the situation in Jerusalem.

00:01:36.519 --> 00:01:40.160
He asked specifically, how are things in Jerusalem?

00:01:40.160 --> 00:01:43.800
Give me a report as to what's going on there,

00:01:43.800 --> 00:01:48.519
and we find that Hanani delivers to Nehemiah this report

00:01:48.519 --> 00:01:52.760
with regard to the great affliction and the reproach.

00:01:52.760 --> 00:01:54.839
He tells him that the wall of Jerusalem

00:01:54.839 --> 00:01:56.480
also is broken down,

00:01:56.480 --> 00:01:59.400
and the gates thereof are burned with fire,

00:01:59.400 --> 00:02:02.839
and we find that Nehemiah, as he received that report

00:02:02.839 --> 00:02:04.800
after that correspondence with Hanani,

00:02:04.800 --> 00:02:08.240
we find that he was very burdened

00:02:08.240 --> 00:02:09.960
for the situation in Jerusalem.

00:02:09.960 --> 00:02:13.559
We find that he immediately went to God in prayer,

00:02:13.559 --> 00:02:16.199
and he began to seek the face of God,

00:02:16.199 --> 00:02:18.600
and we find that chapter number two tells us

00:02:18.600 --> 00:02:21.440
that he was in the presence of Artaxerxes,

00:02:21.440 --> 00:02:23.479
and prior to this particular event,

00:02:23.479 --> 00:02:26.880
he had not been sad in the presence of Artaxerxes,

00:02:26.880 --> 00:02:29.679
but Artaxerxes could see in his countenance

00:02:29.679 --> 00:02:31.559
that he was sad, and he said, what is it?

00:02:31.559 --> 00:02:34.080
This is nothing more than sorrow of heart,

00:02:34.080 --> 00:02:38.199
and we find that Nehemiah reveals to the king

00:02:38.199 --> 00:02:40.399
that which he had heard and understood,

00:02:40.399 --> 00:02:44.360
and permission is granted for Nehemiah to return.

00:02:44.360 --> 00:02:46.600
As you read the rest of chapter number two,

00:02:46.600 --> 00:02:48.979
you find that Nehemiah gets back to the city,

00:02:48.979 --> 00:02:52.059
and he, on his own, upon arrival,

00:02:52.059 --> 00:02:53.779
he goes and he views the city,

00:02:53.779 --> 00:02:55.779
and he's taking everything in,

00:02:55.779 --> 00:02:59.139
and he's seeing firsthand exactly what Hanani

00:02:59.139 --> 00:03:01.300
had described to him in that correspondence

00:03:01.300 --> 00:03:02.539
in chapter number one,

00:03:02.539 --> 00:03:05.740
and we find that Nehemiah then issues a challenge

00:03:05.740 --> 00:03:08.220
to the people of God, those that were there,

00:03:08.220 --> 00:03:12.580
and he tells them, let's rise up and build.

00:03:12.580 --> 00:03:15.779
The good hand of the Lord is upon me.

00:03:15.779 --> 00:03:18.779
And he understood there was a work to be done,

00:03:19.580 --> 00:03:21.539
and we find that immediately upon the challenge

00:03:21.539 --> 00:03:24.020
being issued in Nehemiah chapter number two,

00:03:24.020 --> 00:03:27.020
the opposition also is there.

00:03:27.020 --> 00:03:31.059
I mean, immediately upon Nehemiah saying,

00:03:31.059 --> 00:03:33.259
let us rise up and build,

00:03:33.259 --> 00:03:36.020
the Bible tells us that Sanballat and Tobiah

00:03:36.020 --> 00:03:39.199
were there ready to oppose the work of God.

00:03:40.899 --> 00:03:44.979
Chapter three, four, and five provide us for a record

00:03:44.979 --> 00:03:46.619
not only of those that were there

00:03:46.619 --> 00:03:48.619
in chapter number three extensively,

00:03:49.460 --> 00:03:50.740
but chapters four and five reveal to us

00:03:50.740 --> 00:03:52.699
the work that is being carried on

00:03:52.699 --> 00:03:55.100
and the opposition that they're facing.

00:03:55.100 --> 00:03:57.820
When we come to chapter number six specifically,

00:03:57.820 --> 00:04:02.259
we find that I believe that the enemy begins

00:04:02.259 --> 00:04:05.860
to really up their game, so to speak.

00:04:05.860 --> 00:04:08.179
And we find that as we look at chapter number six

00:04:08.179 --> 00:04:10.979
and dive into this passage this morning,

00:04:10.979 --> 00:04:13.860
I'm trusting that God will help to equip

00:04:13.860 --> 00:04:17.019
and strengthen us as the people of God,

00:04:17.019 --> 00:04:21.059
even as the enemy would seek to derail us.

00:04:21.059 --> 00:04:24.299
We find that it's here in chapter number six

00:04:24.299 --> 00:04:25.579
in verse number one.

00:04:25.579 --> 00:04:27.179
It says, now it came to pass

00:04:27.179 --> 00:04:30.660
when Sanballat and Tobiah and Geshem the Arabian

00:04:30.660 --> 00:04:33.059
and the rest of our enemies heard

00:04:33.059 --> 00:04:35.019
that I had builded the wall

00:04:35.019 --> 00:04:36.779
and that there was no breach left therein,

00:04:36.779 --> 00:04:38.739
and though it says there are parentheses

00:04:38.739 --> 00:04:39.660
at the end of verse number one,

00:04:39.660 --> 00:04:41.059
though at that time I had not set up

00:04:41.059 --> 00:04:42.179
the doors upon the gates,

00:04:42.179 --> 00:04:44.899
notice verse two, that Sanballat and Geshem

00:04:44.899 --> 00:04:46.700
sent unto me saying,

00:04:46.700 --> 00:04:50.579
come, let us meet together in some one of the villages

00:04:50.579 --> 00:04:52.700
in the plain of Ono.

00:04:52.700 --> 00:04:57.019
But they thought to do me mischief.

